[The recommendation for cooking berries before consumption applies only to berries that have been packaged and sold frozen. Fresh berried fruits are likely to be produced locally and are consumed soon after harvesting. Frozen berries are likely to be imported. Earlier reports of hepatitis A virus infection associated with berried fruits in Nordic countries indicated that the contaminated berries originated from the Middle East (Egypt), where hepatitis A contamination of the environment could be considerable. It is surprising that this information appears to have been ignored in Sweden up to the present. - Mod.CP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/20NO.]
